name: Hval by Nicolas Burrows
description: Nicolas Burrows - acclaimed member of the UK-based graphic art collective Nous Vous - created a series of monotypes for his new book "Hvald". Published by Huis Haas in 2012 size: A4 – 24 pages with silkscreened cover They tell a tale of life and death, introspection and abandon. A touching non-verbal story where emotions and nostalgia interlace in fragile black and white images.

name: "The dancer at midnight" zine by Aidan Koch
description: “The Dancer at Midnight” was created by Aidan Koch for her solo show with Huis Haas. In 24 delicate pages she narrates an abstract story of rhythm, time and galaxies, the way only she can. A talented illustrator and graphic artist, Koch draws her pictures with such ease that you are immediately drawn into the visual and poem. 2012 – A5 – 24 pages with silkscreened cover, numbered Published by Huis Haas

name: SPXSF zine
description:
i curated an art show only with brazilian artists at needles and pens called SPXSF
featuring the art of stephan doitschinoff, danielone, carlos dias, silvana mello, diego medina, luciana araujo and pacolli.
60 pages of pure black and white printed in an old copy machine somewhere far in San Francisco, CA. folded and stapled by my hands.

see more here: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CqiDXP8iRXw

i edited this zine with cool stuff from all of us to you, enjoy.
